<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><span _ngcontent-ng-c2462920339="" class="router-outlet-wrapper ng-tns-c2462920339-0"><ms-prompt-chunk _ngcontent-ng-c2317831898="" _nghost-ng-c1653631892="" class="text-chunk ng-star-inserted" id="7DDD7363-E585-485D-93F2-2B5098DC8979"><ms-text-chunk _ngcontent-ng-c1653631892="" _nghost-ng-c3915779407="" class="ng-star-inserted"><ms-cmark-node _ngcontent-ng-c3915779407="" class="cmark-node v3-font-body ng-star-inserted" _nghost-ng-c4139270029=""><p _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"><ms-cmark-node _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" _nghost-ng-c4139270029=""><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">When I type </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">sudoedit /etc/keyd/default.conf</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">, it preserves my nvim stuff. However, the file is created in </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">/var/tmp/...</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"> and I have to exit the editor for the changes to be saved.</span></ms-cmark-node></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"><ms-cmark-node _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" _nghost-ng-c4139270029=""><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">I don't like that, because I would love to just use </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">:w</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"> to save changes and then see the results when I reload the service. I want it to be interactive.</span></ms-cmark-node></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"><ms-cmark-node _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" _nghost-ng-c4139270029=""><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">The command </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">sudo -E nvim /etc/...</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"> doesn't work well; it's not perfect.</span></ms-cmark-node></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"><ms-cmark-node _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" _nghost-ng-c4139270029=""><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">To be honest, </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">sudo nvim /etc/...</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"> is the best method I've found. When I do </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">:w</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">, it saves the changes directly, so I can then press Alt+F9 to reload </span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="inline-code ng-star-inserted">keyd</span><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"> real quick and test the changes almost live. But sadly, this method is not that good either.</span></ms-cmark-node></p><p _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted"><ms-cmark-node _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" _nghost-ng-c4139270029=""><span _ngcontent-ng-c4139270029="" class="ng-star-inserted">Are there any solutions? I'm lost.</span></ms-cmark-node></p></ms-cmark-node></ms-text-chunk></ms-prompt-chunk></span>